Divx/Xvid are pretty much the same encoder. Download the Xvid encoded file chevy, that will work for your ps3.

XviD & DIVX have pretty much the same decoder, & almost every program or bit of hardware that can decode one can also do the other, but the encoders are significantly more different. H.264 has taken the limelight since x264 really got good, but back when Apple & Nero had the best H.264 encoders, XviD was king of the pile. Its encoder can just shove a whole lot more quality into a given filesize than DIVX's can. Go XviD if you can.
